# Finding 100
- Severity: Low
- Pattern type: AI slop; Duplicate `buildRealtimeUrl` helper
- File + line(s): `packages/realtime/realtime-client-runtime/src/shared/runtime.js:89-103`, `apps/jskit-value-app/src/platform/realtime/realtimeRuntime.js:106-120`
- Why it can drift/fail: Realtime URL construction logic is duplicated in both the runtime package and the app wrapper. Any change to URL resolution rules must be synchronized.
- Concrete impact: App realtime runtime can diverge from package behavior, causing inconsistent connection targets.
- Exact remediation: Export `buildRealtimeUrl` from the realtime client runtime and reuse it in the app runtime.

---
Decision: WONT
Justification:
- This change touches app realtime runtime code (client-side), and you requested skipping client-side work while templates are in flux.
Revisit signal:
- Resume client-side work or after the template rewrite lands.
